    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600 Models
        Built Before 05/20/2003 - CAB FEATURES - POWER MIRRORS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0825810">
        <title>POWER MIRRORS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825841">power mirror function diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0825841" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0825891.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Power Mirrors Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEFT MIRROR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. POWER MIRROR SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RIGHT MIRROR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The power mirror feature allows the driver to adjust the upper mirrors for optimal viewing.</para>
            <para>The power mirror switch is directly wired to both mirrors. The mirror controlled by the switch is
                selected with the left/right selector.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
